**For Sale: Charming 2 Bed, 2 Bath Home in Cypress Shores 55+ Community**

Welcome to 73 Perch Street, Winter Haven, FL 33881, located in the desirable Cypress Shores community catering to 55+ residents. To reside here, you must qualify within this vibrant community.

**Key Features:**
- **Boat Docks:** Enjoy the luxury of open dock access with convenient boat slips and community boat ramp, perfect for boating enthusiasts.
- **Community Amenities:** Take advantage of the community gym, rec-room, and clubhouse facilities, fostering an active and social lifestyle.
- **Spacious Home:** This 1986 double wide Homes of Merit property spans 1,032 sq. ft., offering 2 bedrooms and 2 bathrooms.
- **Modern Upgrades:** The home features updated bathrooms, including a walk-in master shower and a tub in the second bath. The kitchen boasts new floors, sink, counters, and energy-efficient LED lighting.
- **Efficient Living:** Benefit from an on-demand water heater, new PEX plumbing installed in March 2023, and energy-efficient window units. The home comes with stainless steel appliances, a washer, and a dryer.
- **Secure Living:** The entry door hardware includes a fingerprint reader for enhanced security.
- **Recent Renovations:** The property has a new metal roof installed in November 2022 and fresh paint inside and out. 
- **Comfortable Living:** Electric couches with USB ports and a senior lift chair are included for your comfort.
-**Luxurious Upgrades:** Level 2 car charger for 11 Kilowatts installed in carport. Home can include 2022 Volkswagen ID.4 Pro S with only 14,000 miles and transferable warranty for an additional $41,000.
- **Cost-Efficient:** The average electric cost is $125 per month, and water/sewer/trash utilities average $25 per month.
- **Parking:** Enjoy the convenience of a two-car parking space.

**Additional Details:**
- **Heating and Cooling:** The home has central air conditioning (cooling) which is currently disconnected from power. However, efficient window units are installed, including an 18,000 BTU unit with heat in the front. Central A/C can be reconnected by seller, if desired.  
- **Financials:** The lot rent for the property is $620+/- per month. Lawn maintenance is necessary, and a transferable termite warranty is available with a fee.
- **Workshop:** The property features large workshops with workbenches, catering to hobbyists and DIY enthusiasts.

Don't miss this opportunity to live in a vibrant community with a private boat dock and modern amenities. For inquiries and showings, please contact Nick.

Come & enjoy Florida living at it's best! Indian Lake Estates surrounds Lake Weohyakapka (locally known as Lake Walk In Water) a 7,500 acre lake known for its outstanding fishing. This charming home is located on one of the most desirable streets in Indian Lake Estates. The home sits on one of the canals that feeds into the lake with a phenomenal view of the lake & pier in the front. The sunsets are gorgeous! Features of this charming home include 3 bedrooms, 2 full baths and 3 car garage. The master suite is very spacious and features a walk-in closet and en suite with 2 separate vanity areas.  On the other side of the home are 2 more nice-sized bedrooms and full bath.  The kitchen features lots of cabinetry and counter space and separate dinette area.  There is also a handy bar for quick meals or to serve food from when entertaining!  The great room is a wonderful gathering place for friends and family.  You will love the cathedral ceilings and decorative wood ceiling beams!  Indian Lake Estates has a boat ramp, marina & the longest fresh water fishing pier in the State of Florida! Other amenities include golfing, shuffle board & basketball courts, 23,000 sq.ft. clubhouse, cafe, post office, churches, library & fitness room. Nature lovers will enjoy the peace & quiet of the country & see deer, raccoon, turkey, turtles, cranes & various species of birds. Orlando & Disney is about an hour's drive north & the Gulf's pristine beaches a little over an hour west. Polk County's best kept secret!
